node.text: The advantage of having friends with a wide variety of skill and experiences, is the never ending flow of good information. This was something that My buddy @joe_farewell recognized when I was really pushing the speed. He identified a lot of unnecessary stress I was placing on parts of my body.  I made the corrections and feel like I am using less energy with better returns.  Obviously I am just point shooting here but I am still picking up sight picture at some point in the presentation, even if it’s after the fact.  @sigsauerinc @safarilandgroup @gcodeholsters @legiontargets #training #speed #performance #alwayslearning

node.text: There is a time and place to minimize your profile but that decision should be purposeful.  Concentrating on your exposure is typically found when you’re being proactive rather than reactive or when cover/concealment is available. Most of the people importing a bunch of non purposeful movement (bending over, blading) prior to engaging the target are simply wasting valuable reaction time.  The get low and blade dudes are generally doing this out of impulse because they lack sufficient training which would allow them to evaluate what gets them on target most efficiently. When you start prioritizing your objectives and let go of the “always do this” or “always do that” made up tactical BS you will find the improvement you so desire. Shooting the weapon is a skill set that is separate from the decision making. Improve the efficiency and accuracy of your shot, then add the appropriate tactic for the situation. @sigsauerinc @safarilandgroup @gcodeholsters @surefire_llc @legiontargets #selfdefense #methods #platform #tactics

node.text: Education is key. There’s really no changing the anti gunners opinion or agenda but I feel the vast majority of non gun owners are an easy sellout when it comes to gun control. This is generally because they have been misinformed and have no vested interest in gun ownership.  By default, if someone has no interest in something and are only fed the negative aspects, why would they care about defending it?  This picture is a perfect example of how outrageous gun restrictions are. Without the proper paperwork, affixing one of these stocks is a felony while the other is ok (for now at least). Do you think the average non gun owner would have any clue as how they’re different or what makes one legal over the other?  More over, does a stock or the size of a rifle materially change its function? Does the round capacity or rate of fire influence the intent of the user? No, because individual conduct is what should be in question.  Social media has limited our ability to reach a broader audience. A few years back when gun content was globally circulated and not censored, I would frequently get questions from non gun owners which gave me an opportunity to educate them.  Now because of this censorship, the anti gunners have full control over feeding them misinformation and influencing their position. It is clear that our greatest advocates right now are organizations like @gunpolicy and @gunownersofamerica to defend our rights. I will continue to donate funds to these organizations and I hope you will too 💪🏼. #gunrights #2ndamendment #2a #freedom #sbr #arpistol #brace #censorship #guncontrol
